WEBVTT

00:01.335 --> 00:03.371
God bless you,
and thank you for tuning in.

00:03.404 --> 00:05.106
(muffled grunting nearby)
Today...

00:05.139 --> 00:08.276
I'm gonna talk to you
about resisting temptation.

00:08.309 --> 00:10.711
Now, we all know
the story from the Bible

00:10.744 --> 00:13.047
of David and Goliath.

00:13.081 --> 00:15.183
(muffled grunting continues)
Champion of the Philistines

00:15.216 --> 00:18.319
versus a much smaller,
weaker opponent,

00:18.352 --> 00:21.289
who simply had the courage
to face him.

00:21.322 --> 00:22.290
(muffled panting)

00:22.323 --> 00:23.591
You see...

00:23.624 --> 00:26.360
David already knew
he had the victory.

00:26.394 --> 00:29.363
He had God on his side.

00:29.397 --> 00:32.733
(muffled grunting)
Goliath can be like that sin

00:32.766 --> 00:34.568
in your life that is

00:34.602 --> 00:37.605
most difficult for you
to overcome, but you...

00:37.638 --> 00:40.341
you can be like David.

00:40.374 --> 00:41.542
With God on your side...

00:41.575 --> 00:44.312
you can slay your giant

00:44.345 --> 00:46.447
and live a life free from sin.

00:46.480 --> 00:48.382
(muffled grunting)

00:48.416 --> 00:50.184
The only question is:

00:50.218 --> 00:52.520
Which sin is your Goliath?

00:52.553 --> 00:55.356
(muffled panting)

00:55.389 --> 00:57.191
*

01:01.262 --> 01:03.831
(phones ringing, beeping;
overlapping conversations)

01:03.864 --> 01:04.765
WOMAN: Did you get this?

01:04.798 --> 01:08.136
MAN: Yeah. What is it?

01:08.169 --> 01:09.403
I don't follow this person.

01:09.437 --> 01:10.838
You got this?
What is this?

01:10.871 --> 01:13.141
What's going on?
Is there an AMBER Alert?

01:13.174 --> 01:14.708
Nothing came up on my phone.

01:14.742 --> 01:15.743
It's an alert from PicThread.

01:15.776 --> 01:17.478
Ah. Well, that
explains it--

01:17.511 --> 01:18.779
I don't do social media.

01:18.812 --> 01:21.282
NELSON: "New post from:
Homestead Harrison"?

01:21.315 --> 01:23.451
I don't follow anyone
named Homestead Harrison.

01:23.484 --> 01:25.486
Neither do I.
RYAN: Well, it looks like

01:25.519 --> 01:27.721
this guy sent an alert
to everyone here.

01:27.755 --> 01:29.690
What the...? Raven, are
you seeing this photo?

01:29.723 --> 01:31.425
No, it's not just everyone
in this room.

01:31.459 --> 01:34.262
Every single user on PicThread
received this photo.

01:35.396 --> 01:37.231
Is this a hoax?

01:37.265 --> 01:38.832
No.

01:38.866 --> 01:41.535
Lividity,
coloring in his fingertips,

01:41.569 --> 01:43.537
purple suggests death, so...

01:43.571 --> 01:46.240
either someone's paying
a lot of attention to detail,

01:46.274 --> 01:47.708
or that guy's definitely dead.

01:47.741 --> 01:49.410
Who posted this?

01:49.443 --> 01:50.811
Um...

01:50.844 --> 01:54.582
Aiden Harrison.
Profile says he lives in Boston.

01:54.615 --> 01:56.517
Check it out.
This post is geo-tagged.

01:56.550 --> 01:57.751
MUNDO:
You have to choose to show

01:57.785 --> 02:00.254
your location on PicThread--
the app doesn't do it for you.

02:00.288 --> 02:01.889
RYAN:
So this Aiden Harrison--
he wanted us

02:01.922 --> 02:03.391
to know where
this photo was taken.

02:03.424 --> 02:07.195
NELSON: Geo-tag says
it's a church in Boston.

02:11.532 --> 02:13.734
(sirens wailing, whooping)

02:13.767 --> 02:17.538
*

02:28.849 --> 02:31.285
MUNDO: It's Aiden Harrison.

02:31.319 --> 02:32.820
Looks like
he's been here a while.

02:32.853 --> 02:34.422
Two or three days,

02:34.455 --> 02:37.491
just from the...
looks and smell of it.

02:37.525 --> 02:39.793
The church is
being renovated.

02:39.827 --> 02:41.595
Bought the killer time
before he sent the photo.

02:41.629 --> 02:42.463
(phone chimes)

02:42.496 --> 02:46.700
Raven just got
a notification from VICAP.

02:46.734 --> 02:49.237
He was reported missing
a week ago.
MUNDO: Killer must have

02:49.270 --> 02:50.671
hijacked his PicThread account.

02:50.704 --> 02:53.607
Why wait to post this picture
till this morning?

02:53.641 --> 02:54.942
And why post it at all?

02:55.976 --> 02:57.311
This is a mess.
There's blood

02:57.345 --> 02:58.712
and bodily fluids
on the ports,

02:58.746 --> 03:00.881
soaked all the way
through to the keyboard.

03:00.914 --> 03:02.950
I'm gonna take everything
back to CTOC,

03:02.983 --> 03:05.519
see if I can retrieve some data.

03:05.553 --> 03:07.488
RUSSELL:
Okey-dokey. (grunts)

03:07.521 --> 03:08.489
Upsy-daisy.

03:08.522 --> 03:10.524
(others groaning)
Oh, snap.

03:10.558 --> 03:13.661
Well, first things first.

03:19.667 --> 03:23.504
The guy's tongue
has been cut out.

03:23.537 --> 03:25.673
Choked to death
on his own blood.

03:27.808 --> 03:30.010
Is that a tattoo?

03:30.043 --> 03:33.647
RUSSELL:
Yeah, it's a... QR code.

03:33.681 --> 03:36.584
Could be a clue
from our killer.

03:40.521 --> 03:43.624
(slow techno music playing)

03:44.992 --> 03:47.595
* Way from me...

03:50.864 --> 03:53.301
* Way from me...

03:56.437 --> 03:58.872
* Way from me...

04:00.941 --> 04:03.577
* Way from me...

04:06.314 --> 04:09.283
* Way from me...

04:11.852 --> 04:14.655
* Way from me...

04:17.925 --> 04:19.293
* Way...

04:19.327 --> 04:20.394
(music ends)

04:20.428 --> 04:21.929
(voice breaking):
He was a good man.

04:21.962 --> 04:23.631
A good father.

04:23.664 --> 04:25.299
A good husband.

04:25.333 --> 04:27.401
Please keep us in your prayers.

04:27.435 --> 04:28.902
Whoever did this

04:28.936 --> 04:31.505
will have to stand before God

04:31.539 --> 04:32.906
and be judged.

04:32.940 --> 04:34.675
RUSSELL:
I can't imagine

04:34.708 --> 04:37.044
losing a loved one
and then finding out about it

04:37.077 --> 04:38.846
on social media
MUNDO:
PicThread removed the photo,

04:38.879 --> 04:41.882
but it's already gone viral--
it's all over the Internet.

04:41.915 --> 04:43.484
Will be forever.

04:43.517 --> 04:44.618
Raven, were you able
to establish how

04:44.652 --> 04:48.456
that photo was sent
to every user?
Well, it's weird.

04:48.489 --> 04:51.559
Everyone-- and I mean
every PicThread subscriber--

04:51.592 --> 04:53.761
was following Pastor Harrison.

04:53.794 --> 04:56.330
RUSSELL:
I know preaching online

04:56.364 --> 04:58.499
is like the pulpit
of the 21st century,

04:58.532 --> 05:00.634
but that's insane--
that many followers?

05:00.668 --> 05:01.635
MUNDO: Yeah, some
of the most popular

05:01.669 --> 05:03.637
televangelists have only
four or five million.

05:03.671 --> 05:05.906
RAMIREZ:
Pastor Harrison's been using
social media for years.

05:05.939 --> 05:08.742
And last week he had
80,000 followers

05:08.776 --> 05:11.078
on PicThread, but today...

05:11.111 --> 05:15.115
he has just over
200 million followers.

05:15.148 --> 05:17.718
How is that possible?
I don't know yet.

05:17.751 --> 05:19.387
It's got to be a hack.
Wait, look at this.

05:19.420 --> 05:21.088
(rapidly keyboarding)
He recently started posting

05:21.121 --> 05:24.692
about overturning laws
on gay marriage

05:24.725 --> 05:26.560
and protesting abortion clinics.

05:26.594 --> 05:27.761
So, that's interesting, right?

05:27.795 --> 05:29.897
If you take a strong stance
against politicized topics,

05:29.930 --> 05:32.800
it makes a bigger
splash online.

05:32.833 --> 05:35.135
Recruit a hell of a lot
more followers that way.

05:35.168 --> 05:37.738
Yeah, but a controversial post
can make people angry.

05:37.771 --> 05:39.773
MUNDO:
Maybe even get you killed.

05:42.676 --> 05:44.077
(typing)

05:46.814 --> 05:48.682
What'd you find, Nelson?
Normal QR code.

05:48.716 --> 05:50.718
Like the ones in all
the magazine ads-- only this one

05:50.751 --> 05:52.620
is linked to a Web site
with a Swedish domain.

05:52.653 --> 05:54.121
Check this out.

05:54.154 --> 05:55.623
Now...

05:55.656 --> 05:57.124
when I scan the QR code

05:57.157 --> 05:58.759
that we found
on Pastor Harrison,

05:58.792 --> 06:00.494
the image sensor on my phone

06:00.528 --> 06:02.763
reads the data--
in this case, a Web address.

06:02.796 --> 06:04.998
RYAN: So what's on the Web site
that that links to?

06:05.032 --> 06:06.567
I have no idea.
I just know the address.

06:06.600 --> 06:07.835
Well, maybe it's
a phishing site

06:07.868 --> 06:10.438
or maybe it dumps malware
onto the network.
Yeah, but see,

06:10.471 --> 06:12.640
I'm thinking of setting up
a isolated connection

06:12.673 --> 06:14.842
to scan the QR code, then we
can see what's on the site.

06:14.875 --> 06:16.744
This phone will be
the only device

06:16.777 --> 06:18.045
that's exposed.

06:18.078 --> 06:19.680
Do it.
A'ight.

06:19.713 --> 06:21.782
That's what I'm talkin' 'bout.

06:21.815 --> 06:24.852
*

06:36.964 --> 06:39.933
Okay, so the only print
I could get off the laptop

06:39.967 --> 06:41.802
belonged to Pastor Harrison.

06:41.835 --> 06:43.904
Well, and before it was covered
in bloody guts and goo,

06:43.937 --> 06:45.706
this was a brand-new laptop.

06:45.739 --> 06:47.775
There's only one
user-generated file in
the entire hard drive.

06:47.808 --> 06:50.611
RUSSELL:
"If you can't say anything nice,

06:50.644 --> 06:52.713
don't say anything at all."

06:52.746 --> 06:54.748
And this wasn't
copied and pasted-- look.

06:54.782 --> 06:55.749
There's typos

06:55.783 --> 06:56.750
in some of the lines--

06:56.784 --> 06:57.451
gets worse as it goes.

06:57.485 --> 06:59.487
When was this document created?

06:59.520 --> 07:01.154
Time stamp says...

07:01.188 --> 07:03.724
three days ago.
So that was after

07:03.757 --> 07:06.527
Pastor Harrison
was reported missing.

07:06.560 --> 07:08.462
So he was taped to the chair

07:08.496 --> 07:12.633
and forced to type this
over and over again.

07:12.666 --> 07:14.802
There's 10,000
lines here.

07:14.835 --> 07:16.604
Even typing 60 words a minute,

07:16.637 --> 07:19.106
that'd take... days.

07:19.139 --> 07:20.307
Someone wanted
to teach him a lesson.

07:20.340 --> 07:24.878
(overlapping conversations,
phones ringing and beeping)

07:24.912 --> 07:26.847
Oh, really? I don't know.

07:26.880 --> 07:29.650
All right,
let's find Avery.

07:29.683 --> 07:30.651
MAN:
I don't know.

07:32.753 --> 07:34.755
Whoa, have you
seen this?
I don't know. How...

07:34.788 --> 07:35.956
Whoa.

07:35.989 --> 07:38.225
This can't be a coincidence.

07:38.258 --> 07:41.529
We just got another photo.
Yeah, I saw.

07:41.562 --> 07:44.498
Another staged murder sent
to everyone on PicThread?

07:44.532 --> 07:46.500
As soon as
we scanned the QR code

07:46.534 --> 07:48.802
and linked to the site,
this message appeared.

07:48.836 --> 07:52.005
RUSSELL: "Some things are better
kept behind closed doors."

07:52.039 --> 07:53.741
Then everyone's
phone went off

07:53.774 --> 07:54.975
with the new
PicThread alert.

07:55.008 --> 07:58.245
So something we did
triggered the release?

07:58.278 --> 08:01.682
So we're looking at one,
maybe two more victims here.

08:01.715 --> 08:02.916
KRUMITZ: Hashtag
#Graphic Warning.

08:02.950 --> 08:04.251
Same as the other photo.

08:04.284 --> 08:05.886
So our target wants us to know

08:05.919 --> 08:07.921
this is connected
to the last killing.

08:07.955 --> 08:09.923
(scoffs)
This is like the Zodiac Killer

08:09.957 --> 08:11.925
sending letters to the press.

08:11.959 --> 08:14.595
RYAN:
We've got a serial killer
who's taunting us

08:14.628 --> 08:15.829
on social media.

08:20.868 --> 08:27.007
* I know you've deceived me,
now here's a surprise *

08:28.942 --> 08:35.282
* I know that you have, 'cause
there's magic in my eyes *

08:35.315 --> 08:38.819
* I can see
for miles and miles *

08:38.852 --> 08:42.856
* I can see for miles
and miles *

08:42.890 --> 08:46.927
* I can see
for miles and miles *

08:46.960 --> 08:50.698
* And miles...

08:50.731 --> 08:51.732
* Oh, yeah.

09:07.915 --> 09:09.617
My phone has been
ringing off the hook

09:09.650 --> 09:11.018
about photos
on PicThread.

09:11.051 --> 09:12.620
The president's own children
received them.

09:12.653 --> 09:14.688
He called me himself
for answers.

09:14.722 --> 09:16.657
I'm hoping you have some.

09:16.690 --> 09:18.091
Both photos were geo-tagged.

09:18.125 --> 09:20.127
Local law enforcement
are on their way

09:20.160 --> 09:21.228
to the second location.

09:21.261 --> 09:22.896
We're not far behind.
And I understand

09:22.930 --> 09:25.198
our Cyber Division
is responsible

09:25.232 --> 09:27.267
for the second photo
being released?
When that page loaded

09:27.300 --> 09:30.671
here at CTOC, it ran a script
that automatically posted

09:30.704 --> 09:32.773
the next photo to PicThread.

09:32.806 --> 09:36.276
The target wanted the FBI to be
responsible for sending it out.

09:36.309 --> 09:38.345
I promise you, this
will not happen again.

09:38.378 --> 09:39.379
Good.

09:39.412 --> 09:41.381
(indistinct chatter)

09:41.414 --> 09:43.617
(elevator bell dings)

09:44.652 --> 09:45.919
*

09:48.188 --> 09:49.757
Aw, come on,
you can't spare

09:49.790 --> 09:51.358
an hour for your old man?

09:51.391 --> 09:53.226
Dad, I'm so sorry. I...

09:53.260 --> 09:54.361
You have to cancel
our lunch.

09:54.394 --> 09:56.630
This case just
came in. It's...

09:56.664 --> 09:57.497
I understand.

09:57.530 --> 10:00.100
But, uh... can we
talk for a minute?

10:01.134 --> 10:02.402
It's important.

10:02.435 --> 10:03.403
Yeah. Yeah.

10:03.436 --> 10:05.806
Um... come on.

10:11.044 --> 10:12.713
You okay?

10:13.881 --> 10:14.848
Still have cancer.

10:14.882 --> 10:16.183
Chemo sucks.

10:16.216 --> 10:17.617
Otherwise, I'm fine.

10:19.753 --> 10:21.288
It's about you and Devon.

10:21.321 --> 10:23.123
The other day, when
I was with Michelle,

10:23.156 --> 10:24.792
she said...

10:24.825 --> 10:26.927
"Mommy and Daddy
have been fighting."

10:26.960 --> 10:28.929
It's nothing for you to be...

10:28.962 --> 10:30.330
Who's Nina?

10:31.699 --> 10:33.166
Michelle mentioned her.

10:34.334 --> 10:38.138
Nina is a bartender
at Conaghan's Pub.

10:38.171 --> 10:40.007
Why? What did Michelle say
about Nina?

10:40.040 --> 10:42.342
She heard her name

10:42.375 --> 10:43.977
when you were fighting.

10:46.379 --> 10:48.415
Are you having an affair?

10:49.449 --> 10:51.384
Dad...
You can be honest

10:51.418 --> 10:52.853
with me, son.
Come on.

10:52.886 --> 10:55.188
No.

10:55.222 --> 10:58.191
I'm trying
to make it work with Devon.

10:58.225 --> 11:01.228
A few months ago,
I-I went to Conaghan's Pub

11:01.261 --> 11:04.732
a couple times. Nina was
working there. We chatted.

11:04.765 --> 11:06.734
Next thing I know,
she's become friends with Devon,

11:06.767 --> 11:08.401
she's trying to come between us.

11:08.435 --> 11:10.103
Oh, hey.
Hey.

11:10.137 --> 11:13.106
Perfect timing. We were just
about to sit down for dinner.

11:13.140 --> 11:15.976
This is my friend Nina,
from spin class.

11:16.009 --> 11:17.477
She's gonna join us.

11:17.510 --> 11:18.345
NINA:
Devon, this is so crazy.

11:18.378 --> 11:20.981
Elijah and I actually
know each other.

11:21.014 --> 11:22.883
He comes to my bar
all the time.

11:22.916 --> 11:25.819
You see what's going on here?
You see what she started?
Elijah,

11:25.853 --> 11:27.788
is there something more
you want to tell me?

11:27.821 --> 11:30.457
The woman is delusional.
And then, out of nowhere,

11:30.490 --> 11:32.760
the other night, she texted me.

11:32.793 --> 11:34.795
Devon saw the text

11:34.828 --> 11:38.131
come through.
You know, it was a thing.

11:38.165 --> 11:40.801
But it's fine. We're fine.

11:40.834 --> 11:42.803
Hmm.

11:42.836 --> 11:44.504
You sure?

11:44.537 --> 11:45.939
Yeah.

11:47.808 --> 11:48.776
Don't worry about it.

11:49.476 --> 11:51.311
Dinner this weekend?

11:51.344 --> 11:52.813
Why not tonight?

11:52.846 --> 11:54.915
Flying to Boston.

11:54.948 --> 11:56.950
*

12:03.123 --> 12:05.759
MUNDO: Nicole Hogan,
24 years old,

12:05.793 --> 12:07.394
third-year
graduate student.

12:07.427 --> 12:09.763
This is her place.
Photo was posted to her account.

12:09.797 --> 12:10.998
Greg Roberts, 25.

12:11.031 --> 12:12.833
He lives across town.

12:12.866 --> 12:15.102
No PicThread account that we
could find. Initial body temp

12:15.135 --> 12:16.904
suggests they haven't
been dead long.

12:16.937 --> 12:18.505
Nine, ten hours at the most.

12:18.538 --> 12:22.042
No rigor.

12:22.075 --> 12:24.878
And look at this.
He's-he's clenching

12:24.912 --> 12:26.947
the selfie stick.

12:26.980 --> 12:29.516
So maybe a cadaveric spasm.

12:31.251 --> 12:33.921
No, I'm wrong.

12:36.890 --> 12:39.259
It's glued to his hand.

12:39.292 --> 12:40.894
MUNDO:
The killer was kind enough

12:40.928 --> 12:43.263
to leave us the camera.

12:43.296 --> 12:45.799
RUSSELL:
Blood pool left a void,

12:45.833 --> 12:49.036
suggesting that Nicole
was shot first at...

12:49.069 --> 12:50.303
point-blank range.

12:54.507 --> 12:56.810
RYAN: The shooter
needed the picture,

12:56.844 --> 12:58.879
so Greg was held at gunpoint.

12:58.912 --> 13:02.015
He dragged Nicole towards him,

13:02.049 --> 13:04.017
was forced to take

13:04.051 --> 13:05.886
a selfie.

13:05.919 --> 13:09.890
And Greg was shot
in the head.

13:09.923 --> 13:12.559
Splattered all over the wall.

13:12.592 --> 13:14.127
MUNDO: Someone went through
an awful lot of trouble

13:14.161 --> 13:16.296
to stage a photo
to post on PicThread.

13:16.329 --> 13:17.297
RUSSELL:
For the second time,

13:17.330 --> 13:18.899
right?

13:18.932 --> 13:21.168
Pastor Harrison's murder
was staged also.

13:21.201 --> 13:23.003
RYAN: Yeah, that's
what I don't get.

13:23.036 --> 13:25.572
How are these victims
related to Pastor Harrison?

13:25.605 --> 13:27.841
How are they connected?

13:28.876 --> 13:31.544
RUSSELL:
Okay.

13:31.578 --> 13:34.214
Got another QR code.

13:34.247 --> 13:35.883
MUNDO:
There's your connection.

13:35.916 --> 13:38.018
And maybe another victim.

13:42.589 --> 13:44.591
(crying)
(pipe organ playing)

13:54.601 --> 13:57.104
I'm so sorry
for your loss.

13:57.137 --> 13:58.605
Thank you.

13:58.638 --> 14:00.140
(crying)

14:44.952 --> 14:45.953
(tapping keys)

14:57.965 --> 14:59.232
KRUMITZ:
I did it.

14:59.266 --> 15:01.068
I discovered how the photos
were blasted out

15:01.101 --> 15:03.403
to over 200 million
PicThread users.

15:03.436 --> 15:06.206
I found what's called
a force-follow bug attached

15:06.239 --> 15:07.707
to Aiden Harrison's profile.

15:07.740 --> 15:09.943
It's extra code
that forces anyone

15:09.977 --> 15:12.946
that visits the pastor's page
to follow him automatically.

15:12.980 --> 15:15.482
Then that code gets
copied to their profiles

15:15.515 --> 15:18.118
and spreads to their followers
and so on and so forth.

15:18.151 --> 15:20.553
It's like what happened with
MySpace all those years ago.

15:20.587 --> 15:23.957
They had to shut down the site
